Rating: 0
I'm not going to give this any stars, because I made a major-ish substitution. I used thick, Greek yogurt + splash of heavy cream in place of sour cream, because that's what I had. Normally, this works fine, and it worked this time (meaning, I tempered it, so it didn't curdle, etc.) The sauce was smooth and unbroken. But this was a huge pile of YUCK. Seriously, I can't remember the last time I made such a flop of a meal. I'm a pretty experienced cook, and I can normally fix a recipe that goes off the rails, but this was a major exception. It looked terrible, and tasted nearly as bad. In the end, we resorted to Tabasco and red wine vinegar in an attempt to salvage it ... ugh. The problem could be my paprika, which was an unopened, BRAND NEW tin of Szegd (sp?) sweet Hungarian. The expiration date is Dec. 2010, but I think it went stale anyway (there goes $10). It's the only thing that explains why this recipe looked and tasted like ground cardboard. Moral of the story? Test your paprika flavor first... it could save your dinner.

