Rating: 1
I have a fabulous chicken paprikas recipie that puts this to shame follow the same directions until you add the onions. First of all use 2 cups thinly sliced onion and saute until very soft. Then add 2T Hungarian paprika and 2T flour. Cook for 1 min. Add 1 1/2-2C chicken broth. Add chicken back in and cook until done. Remove chicken and cook the sauce down until almost pasty (this is the secret). It takes about an hour at a high simmer. Then add the sour cream 1-1 1/2 cups. It is the best thing you ever tasted.

